title: For Sale/Trade:  Sauer 202 Lightweight Bolt Gun - .243
postcontent:
The Sauer 202 series is a bolt-action repeating rifle of modular design allowing the customer to easily replace individual components and convert calibers. Clamp screws connect the barrel and the receiver and the trigger assembly is built into the receiver as a separate module. The main stock and the forend are connected to this "self-supporting" unit without having any supporting function themselves. The results are better accuracy because any natural warping of wood stocks cannot influence it. The bolt locks up directly into the barrel leaving the receiver as an unstressed part.

This rifle is pretty much the nicest I've held. It's beautiful. My buddy's dad brought it down from CO and asked me to find a new home for it. So here it is. Will come with the mount and rings. The Swarovski comes off unless it is something you can't live without and we make an agreeable trade/sale.

This rifle will also come with about 150-200 rounds (i'll count a little later) of premium ammo. Every weight and projectile configuration one can find - all Hornady - and you can figure out what groups best for you. About 100 rounds through the rifle and meticulously cleaned and maintained.
